1
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:40,140
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:43,130
[Episode 34]

3
00:01:44,789 --> 00:01:46,190
Why are you looking at me?

4
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:49,729
You look great in this outfit.

5
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:54,180
Just as good as back then.

6
00:02:05,350 --> 00:02:05,850
Look.

7
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,480
Comrade Bai Ju, stop laughing.

8
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,370
It's your turn.

9
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:24,070
I want to set up a forestry police unit.

10
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:27,180
I saw this at home a few days ago.

11
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,770
So I transferred it to my phone.

12
00:02:31,730 --> 00:02:33,590
I thought you might want to see it.

13
00:02:39,140 --> 00:02:40,000
It would be best

14
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:41,190
if we could also get

15
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,460
a helicopter.

16
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:45,579
With 40,000 square kilometers,

17
00:02:45,810 --> 00:02:47,840
patrolling the mountains
would only take a day.

18
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,430
Then just fly

19
00:02:48,430 --> 00:02:49,500
straight back to the county

20
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,030
and go home to take a shower.

21
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:53,050
That would be pure bliss.

22
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:54,890
It feels like...

23
00:02:58,250 --> 00:02:59,710
a lifetime ago.

24
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:04,010
I can't believe

25
00:03:04,010 --> 00:03:05,240
I used to do that.

26
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:12,350
Captain.

27
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:14,790
Your turn.

28
00:03:15,550 --> 00:03:16,550
Give us a summary.

29
00:03:17,970 --> 00:03:19,430
Let me talk about my dream.

30
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,340
I hope that in the future,

31
00:03:24,410 --> 00:03:25,000
the world

32
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:27,090
will no longer need nature reserves.

33
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:37,340
Bai Ju.

34
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:41,270
All these years,

35
00:03:41,270 --> 00:03:42,730
you haven't changed a bit.

36
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:44,079
All these years,

37
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:45,210
along the way,

38
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:48,280
you could give up anything.

39
00:03:49,860 --> 00:03:51,460
But I believe you won't stop.

40
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:54,270
Besides, you're divorced now.

41
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,160
You can't stop.

42
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:58,510
You can't.

43
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:36,850
Director Huang, Director Huang.

44
00:04:36,850 --> 00:04:37,550
About this regreening project,

45
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:38,159
wasn't it agreed

46
00:04:38,159 --> 00:04:39,220
that 2 companies would do it together?

47
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:39,630
Why has it now

48
00:04:39,630 --> 00:04:41,010
gone solely to Xinhai?

49
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:41,659
Exactly.

50
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:42,640
The regreening area is so huge,

51
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:43,950
and you just give it all to them?

52
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,130
We have technical teams too.

53
00:04:45,130 --> 00:04:45,830
We can guarantee

54
00:04:45,830 --> 00:04:46,570
the quality.

55
00:04:46,610 --> 00:04:48,440
Didn't I tell you?

56
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:50,790
I don't have the final say on this.

57
00:04:50,810 --> 00:04:52,670
The city has issued the document.

58
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:54,280
Didn't you hear what Mayor Wang said

59
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:55,610
at the meeting just now?

60
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:57,800
Alright, alright.

61
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,600
It's settled.

62
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:00,030
Director Huang.

63
00:05:00,950 --> 00:05:01,780
Director Huang!

64
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:02,520
Forget it.

65
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,250
Don't you get it?

66
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:06,590
Mayor Wang decided this.

67
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:07,910
The original plan to have 2 companies

68
00:05:07,910 --> 00:05:08,890
do the regreening project

69
00:05:08,890 --> 00:05:10,350
was proposed by Vice Mayor Lin.

70
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:12,060
He didn't even show up today.

71
00:05:13,070 --> 00:05:13,690
Forget it.

72
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:14,830
Let's go. Let's go.

73
00:05:15,140 --> 00:05:15,970
Let's go.

74
00:05:21,980 --> 00:05:22,640
Mayor Wang,

75
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:23,300
take care.

76
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:25,810
Goodbye, Mr. Feng.

77
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:46,420
Chun.

78
00:05:47,090 --> 00:05:48,330
How much severance pay do you think

79
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:49,530
the mine will give us?

80
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:51,570
Who told you

81
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:53,070
we're being laid off?

82
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,480
Where's your

83
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,610
"Don't believe or spread rumors" now?

84
00:05:56,659 --> 00:05:58,320
Do we really need to hear it from others?

85
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,120
Those with connections

86
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,130
are already looking for their next job.

87
00:06:00,130 --> 00:06:00,570
It's just us

88
00:06:00,570 --> 00:06:02,430
who are still stuck here waiting.

89
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:07,020
The group spent a fortune

90
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:08,970
on the integration before.

91
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:10,930
There's not much left in the accounts now.

92
00:06:10,930 --> 00:06:12,070
I heard from Mr. Meng

93
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,010
that the whole group

94
00:06:13,010 --> 00:06:14,410
is struggling right now.

95
00:06:14,770 --> 00:06:16,030
The severance package

96
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,640
won't be ready anytime soon.

97
00:06:18,030 --> 00:06:18,970
Don't worry.

98
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,340
Just wait a bit longer.

99
00:06:21,170 --> 00:06:21,980
Wait?

100
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,060
Let me tell you,

101
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:23,870
that Meng guy

102
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:24,930
is just fooling you.

103
00:06:24,930 --> 00:06:25,860
Struggling?

104
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:27,220
Those coal bosses

105
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:28,000
are only thinking about

106
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,510
how to stuff more money

107
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:29,800
into their own pockets.

108
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,430
Exactly.

109
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:31,560
They surely have enough money

110
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,180
to last them for their next lives.

111
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:34,250
Now that they're done with the mine,

112
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:36,310
they can take the money and live it up.

113
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,860
What's that phrase again?

114
00:06:39,180 --> 00:06:40,110
Anyway, it means

115
00:06:40,350 --> 00:06:41,180
being totally free.

116
00:06:41,180 --> 00:06:43,220
You mean financial freedom?

117
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,070
No.

118
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:44,800
M-Mr. Meng.

119
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:45,350
Mr. Meng.

120
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:46,540
Having lunch?

121
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,770
Have you eaten, Mr. Meng?

122
00:06:47,770 --> 00:06:49,170
I have. You guys go ahead.

123
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:50,980
You guys chat.

124
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:52,020
We will head out first.

125
00:06:52,020 --> 00:06:53,220
Right, right, right.

126
00:06:54,230 --> 00:06:54,810
Goodbye.

127
00:07:01,370 --> 00:07:01,930
Mr. Meng.

128
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,740
Don't take it to heart.

129
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:05,480
Mining suspension

130
00:07:05,490 --> 00:07:07,220
is hard for everyone to accept.

131
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:08,250
Those two were actually

132
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,180
being polite.

133
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,620
You haven't heard about

134
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,730
what those workers from Mine No. 2 said.

135
00:07:11,730 --> 00:07:12,660
It's much worse.

136
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:13,700
Mine No. 2?

137
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:16,680
After Wu Jiang's accident,

138
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,240
didn't Mine No. 2

139
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,970
become completely unmanaged?

140
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:19,980
These past few days,

141
00:07:19,980 --> 00:07:20,560
I've been cleaning up

142
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,660
this mess for him.

143
00:07:22,890 --> 00:07:24,680
As the assistant to the General Manager,

144
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,210
you're neglecting your duties.

145
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:27,940
You don't even think to help me.

146
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:29,800
Mining is fully banned now.

147
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,130
What else is there to do?

148
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:32,810
Regreening.

149
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,120
You have experience with this.

150
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,700
Didn't your Mine No. 1

151
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:37,360
research

152
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:39,040
grass planting technology before?

153
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:39,510
We just

154
00:07:39,540 --> 00:07:41,240
did a few experiments on our own.

155
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,570
But when we reported it,

156
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,670
the group wasn't very interested,

157
00:07:43,670 --> 00:07:44,940
so we didn't continue.

158
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:47,540
Times have changed.

159
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:48,990
Now,

160
00:07:49,020 --> 00:07:50,420
this is the top priority.

161
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,159
Xinhai will take over

162
00:07:53,159 --> 00:07:54,960
the mine's regreening project.

163
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,260
So,

164
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:57,720
are you up for the job?

165
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:01,060
That's a good thing.

166
00:08:01,770 --> 00:08:02,710
Does that mean

167
00:08:02,740 --> 00:08:03,310
the company can

168
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:04,390
keep some staff

169
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,900
to carry out the project?

170
00:08:05,910 --> 00:08:07,430
We need to control the numbers

171
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:08,760
to avoid overstaffing.

172
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:10,310
Those two buddies of yours...

173
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:10,890
They did a pretty good job

174
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:11,950
in planting grass.

175
00:08:11,980 --> 00:08:13,120
They were the most active.

176
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,640
With the layoffs, can we...

177
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,100
You've got the wrong idea.

178
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,760
I want to borrow them from you.

179
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:20,590
Transfer them to Mine No. 2

180
00:08:20,590 --> 00:08:21,570
to work on the regreening project

181
00:08:21,570 --> 00:08:22,220
to help me.

182
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,420
No problem.

183
00:08:24,690 --> 00:08:25,250
Come in.

184
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,360
Mr. Meng, are you in a meeting?

185
00:08:27,850 --> 00:08:28,390
The room you asked for

186
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:29,060
is ready.

187
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,690
How would you like it set up?

188
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:31,710
Cleaning up a room?

189
00:08:31,710 --> 00:08:32,370
Let me help.

190
00:08:32,669 --> 00:08:33,289
Bai Chun.

191
00:08:35,169 --> 00:08:36,570
I'm just clearing out a room

192
00:08:36,570 --> 00:08:37,630
to store some junk.

193
00:08:38,179 --> 00:08:39,240
You go do your work.

194
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:44,900
Don't make copies

195
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:46,460
of this key for anyone else.

196
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,340
I'll keep it.

197
00:08:48,020 --> 00:08:48,950
Got it, Mr. Meng.

198
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:56,280
[Kunlun Restaurant]

199
00:09:01,770 --> 00:09:02,320
Yunfei.

200
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:03,810
You're here.

201
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,390
Two boxed meals.

202
00:09:05,470 --> 00:09:06,670
One meat, one veggie.

203
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:07,170
Okay.

204
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:08,870
No, no, no.

205
00:09:08,970 --> 00:09:09,580
Use mine.

206
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,150
Sure.

207
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,100
Mr. Bai.

208
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:25,540
How's it going?

209
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:30,410
The coal mine shut down just like that.

210
00:09:30,410 --> 00:09:31,320
Those bosses

211
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,660
are getting ready to move out.

212
00:09:32,660 --> 00:09:33,920
Every time I go collect debt,

213
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:35,320
they just tell me to wait.

214
00:09:35,510 --> 00:09:36,030
If I wait any longer,

215
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:37,630
my restaurant will go under.

216
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:40,800
What does this mean?

217
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:44,340
It's payment for the debt.

218
00:09:45,410 --> 00:09:46,670
They paid me with a dog.

219
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,100
It's alright.

220
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,290
Selling boxed meals is fine too.

221
00:09:52,290 --> 00:09:53,010
It's good.

222
00:09:53,090 --> 00:09:54,620
Zhuling loves boxed meals.

223
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:55,120
I guess

224
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,780
you're back to your old trade.

225
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:59,800
Worst case, I'll close the restaurant

226
00:09:59,910 --> 00:10:01,310
and go be a househusband.

227
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:02,410
Yan

228
00:10:02,890 --> 00:10:04,360
is about to become Chief Physician.

229
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,070
Isn't that great?

230
00:10:05,070 --> 00:10:06,480
If I'm a househusband,

231
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:08,050
I'll just cook for her alone.

232
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:08,980
I-I'll take care of her.

233
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:10,180
Take good care of her.

234
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:11,860
Living off your wife, huh?

235
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:12,280
What?

236
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,250
So?

237
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,410
What's wrong with living off my wife?

238
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:17,100
Someone can't pull it off
even if they try.

239
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,410
You can just eat these...

240
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:19,810
bachelor's boxed meals.

241
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:25,770
Hello.

242
00:10:29,010 --> 00:10:29,550
Alright.

243
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,440
Sure, no problem.

244
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:33,110
Okay, okay.

245
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:33,600
See you later.

246
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,660
Alright, alright.

247
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:35,640
Who was that?

248
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:37,680
Your sister.

249
00:10:37,780 --> 00:10:38,240
My sister?

250
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,040
She called me.

251
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:40,050
My sister called you?

252
00:10:40,050 --> 00:10:41,310
Your sister called me.

253
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:42,840
I don't need the boxed meals.

254
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:43,240
Look at

255
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,770
that smug look on your face.

256
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:47,910
Since you don't need the boxed meals,

257
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:48,650
you don't want your box back?

258
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:49,980
I'll leave the box here.

259
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:57,760
I don't even want this restaurant anymore.

260
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,150
Uncle Lin.

261
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,040
Uncle Lin.

262
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:23,250
Uncle Lin.

263
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,270
I really can't keep up with you.

264
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:24,940
Bai Ji.

265
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:26,320
You...

266
00:11:27,210 --> 00:11:27,790
I thought

267
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:29,920
it was those small mine owners again.

268
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:31,460
Sorry to disturb you.

269
00:11:32,270 --> 00:11:32,870
It's the first time

270
00:11:32,870 --> 00:11:34,330
I've seen you exercising.

271
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:35,460
Business isn't busy,

272
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:36,920
so I thought I'd exercise.

273
00:11:40,190 --> 00:11:41,170
Your restaurant

274
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,960
must have been affected quite a bit.

275
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:45,900
Uncle Lin.

276
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:48,920
There is something

277
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,320
I'd like to discuss with you.

278
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:53,410
Uncle Lin.

279
00:11:54,460 --> 00:11:55,720
Is this request of mine

280
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,560
making things harder for you

281
00:11:57,890 --> 00:11:59,550
than those small mine owners?

282
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:00,540
Yes.

283
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:04,000
Bai Ji.

284
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,610
Regreening is a good thing.

285
00:12:08,860 --> 00:12:10,200
But if you want to bid,

286
00:12:11,130 --> 00:12:12,930
I can't put in a good word for you.

287
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:16,860
Everything must be legal,

288
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:17,760
compliant,

289
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,820
and fair.

290
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:27,210
But if you are

291
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:30,620
really interested,

292
00:12:31,410 --> 00:12:32,140
I can help you

293
00:12:32,150 --> 00:12:34,050
by introducing a technology company.

294
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:34,790
Go find them first

295
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:35,650
and learn more.

296
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:37,240
Okay, okay.

297
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:37,970
That's great.

298
00:12:37,970 --> 00:12:39,170
Thank you, Uncle Lin.

299
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:42,530
Back then,

300
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:45,950
when you came back from
the Tanggula Road Maintenance Squad,

301
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:47,470
I told your mother

302
00:12:47,650 --> 00:12:48,710
that this decision

303
00:12:48,910 --> 00:12:50,770
would affect the child's future.

304
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:54,130
Later, when you got your own restaurant,

305
00:12:54,470 --> 00:12:55,730
I was happy for you too.

306
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,670
Now that you want to switch

307
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:01,390
to the regreening business,

308
00:13:01,730 --> 00:13:03,240
you need to think it through.

309
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,900
This is a long-term endeavor.

310
00:13:05,230 --> 00:13:06,760
You won't make quick money.

311
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:07,980
But

312
00:13:08,590 --> 00:13:10,650
it will benefit future generations.

313
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,450
I think it's very meaningful.

314
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:18,350
Changqing Ecological Technology Company.

315
00:13:19,570 --> 00:13:21,100
A grass-planting company.

316
00:13:21,330 --> 00:13:22,000
This name

317
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:23,050
sounds quite grand.

318
00:13:23,050 --> 00:13:23,760
Of course.

319
00:13:26,050 --> 00:13:27,510
Have you made up your mind?

320
00:13:28,170 --> 00:13:29,300
I've made up my mind.

321
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:30,860
I'm selling the restaurant.

322
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:31,790
I'm done with it.

323
00:13:32,530 --> 00:13:33,940
The regreening business

324
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:36,370
is more profitable

325
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,770
and has a better future.

326
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:39,860
If I do it well,

327
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:41,410
it will benefit future generations.

328
00:13:41,410 --> 00:13:42,470
It's a great cause.

329
00:13:42,650 --> 00:13:44,320
Don't make it sound so big.

330
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,080
To do this,

331
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:48,300
how much do you want to invest?

332
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:50,100
I discussed it with Chun.

333
00:13:50,410 --> 00:13:51,670
This regreening project

334
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:52,790
is related to his work,

335
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:53,850
so he can't invest,

336
00:13:53,990 --> 00:13:55,590
but he'll lend me some money.

337
00:13:55,820 --> 00:13:58,220
Plus the money from selling the restaurant

338
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:00,100
and my savings over the years,

339
00:14:00,290 --> 00:14:00,980
I can acquire

340
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:02,410
50% of the shares.

341
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:06,900
But I think

342
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:08,890
if we're going to do it,

343
00:14:09,030 --> 00:14:09,960
we should go big.

344
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:11,890
Now, Mr. Chang

345
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,630
has agreed to transfer

346
00:14:12,630 --> 00:14:14,340
80% of the shares.

347
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,730
What's in it for him, then?

348
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,030
He worked so hard to build the business.

349
00:14:20,030 --> 00:14:22,030
Why would he just hand it over to you?

350
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:23,690
You don't understand, Mom.

351
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,090
First,

352
00:14:26,470 --> 00:14:27,950
the market for grass seeds

353
00:14:28,580 --> 00:14:30,790
is usually very niche.

354
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:32,940
It's only because we've caught

355
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:33,910
the wind

356
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,320
of this regreening project.

357
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:36,310
So there's a chance

358
00:14:36,310 --> 00:14:37,780
for mass production.

359
00:14:37,890 --> 00:14:38,530
Second,

360
00:14:38,890 --> 00:14:40,290
they are pressed for time.

361
00:14:40,290 --> 00:14:40,930
He can't find

362
00:14:40,930 --> 00:14:41,460
a suitable investor

363
00:14:41,460 --> 00:14:42,650
in the short term.

364
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,560
Without our investment,

365
00:14:44,670 --> 00:14:45,270
he can't produce

366
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:46,270
on a large scale.

367
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:47,120
So,

368
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:48,270
on the surface,

369
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:50,010
it looks like they're taking a hit.

370
00:14:50,010 --> 00:14:51,320
But as long as the project
gets off the ground,

371
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,650
the actual money earned

372
00:14:52,890 --> 00:14:54,550
will be much more than before.

373
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:57,840
What did you mean

374
00:14:57,940 --> 00:14:59,200
by "pressed for time"?

375
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,120
This isn't just business.

376
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:02,890
It's a task assigned from above.

377
00:15:02,890 --> 00:15:04,180
They have to complete

378
00:15:04,390 --> 00:15:07,120
the pilot project in Xinhai
within the deadline.

379
00:15:07,170 --> 00:15:08,050
In Xinhai?

380
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:10,930
Yes.

381
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:14,220
Xinhai is in charge of the coal mine's
regreening project.

382
00:15:14,410 --> 00:15:14,940
I'm warning you,

383
00:15:14,940 --> 00:15:16,270
don't work with Xinhai.

384
00:15:17,090 --> 00:15:18,820
There might be problems there.

385
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:19,750
Problems?

386
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:21,130
Is there something wrong
with Chun's workplace?

387
00:15:21,130 --> 00:15:23,130
Don't listen to Ju's nonsense, Mom.

388
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,520
This is a task assigned by the province.

389
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:26,050
Xinhai is just a pilot site.

390
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:27,130
What kind of problems could there be?

391
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:27,730
Besides,

392
00:15:27,870 --> 00:15:28,820
the first pilot site

393
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:30,100
is at Chun's mine.

394
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:31,600
He's in charge.

395
00:15:31,650 --> 00:15:32,620
Would he scam me?

396
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:35,890
I'm a public official.

397
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:38,800
I can't be involved
in investment or business.

398
00:15:39,070 --> 00:15:39,480
This matter

399
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,810
originally didn't have much to do with me.

400
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:42,810
But I still want to advise you

401
00:15:42,810 --> 00:15:44,340
to think it over carefully.

402
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,180
If this is really such a good thing,

403
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,580
why didn't the company

404
00:15:48,670 --> 00:15:50,400
find someone else to take over?

405
00:15:50,740 --> 00:15:51,620
Why would such a good opportunity

406
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:53,020
fall right into your lap?

407
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:53,720
Why

408
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:55,220
can't it fall into my lap?

409
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,220
Why can't I

410
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:57,460
have a little bit of good luck?

411
00:15:57,460 --> 00:15:58,430
Do I always have to be unlucky?

412
00:15:58,430 --> 00:15:59,820
That's not what I meant.

413
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:00,890
Why are you getting so worked up?

414
00:16:00,890 --> 00:16:01,930
I think it's fine.

415
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:07,680
Ms. Bai has stated her position.

416
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:08,130
Come on,

417
00:16:08,130 --> 00:16:09,340
analyze it for us.

418
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,250
Why do some people

419
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,780
work hard their whole lives

420
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:19,270
but never make much money,

421
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:21,020
while others

422
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:23,210
can seize opportunities
and make a fortune?

423
00:16:23,210 --> 00:16:24,810
The key lies in information.

424
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,170
For most people,

425
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:27,960
the channels to obtain

426
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,500
effective information

427
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,410
immediately

428
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,460
are very limited.

429
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:31,640
But the channel Bai Ji used

430
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,440
to get the information this time

431
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,770
came from Uncle Lin.

432
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:36,100
Exactly.

433
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:38,550
A company recommended by Uncle Lin.

434
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,800
A path he pointed out.

435
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,320
You really know your stuff, Shao.

436
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,500
A real career woman.

437
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:44,890
An entrepreneur.

438
00:16:44,890 --> 00:16:46,290
Stop the nonsense.

439
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:47,670
Just tell us the truth,

440
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:50,020
how much capital are you short?

441
00:16:51,170 --> 00:16:53,730
The transfer fee for my restaurant
is one million.

442
00:16:53,730 --> 00:16:55,080
Chun lent me some money.

443
00:16:56,050 --> 00:16:57,150
Plus my savings,

444
00:16:57,180 --> 00:16:59,110
I can scrape together one million.

445
00:16:59,650 --> 00:17:01,250
I'm still short one million.

446
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:02,620
That much?

447
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:04,430
Mom.

448
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:06,900
Mom.

449
00:17:08,839 --> 00:17:10,119
My fixed deposit

450
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:11,270
can't be withdrawn.

451
00:17:11,770 --> 00:17:13,640
I can only take out 100,000 now.

452
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:16,250
Is investing in you

453
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:17,349
gonna give a higher return
than the bank interest?

454
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:18,089
Yes,

455
00:17:18,220 --> 00:17:19,260
much higher than

456
00:17:19,290 --> 00:17:20,400
the bank's fixed deposit rate.

457
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,160
The bank gives 3

458
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:21,890
to 4 percent.

459
00:17:22,460 --> 00:17:23,270
I'll give you 14

460
00:17:23,270 --> 00:17:24,069
or 15 percent.

461
00:17:24,089 --> 00:17:24,950
Either is fine.

462
00:17:25,630 --> 00:17:26,740
That high?

463
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:30,750
This isn't illegal fundraising, is it?

464
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:31,810
You need to spend less time
on the internet

465
00:17:31,810 --> 00:17:32,590
for the wrong information.

466
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:33,880
What illegal fundraising?

467
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:36,410
There's a police officer
sitting right here.

468
00:17:36,910 --> 00:17:38,610
Ju, tell Mom,

469
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,220
is this illegal fundraising?

470
00:17:40,220 --> 00:17:40,830
This counts as

471
00:17:40,830 --> 00:17:42,460
a loan between family members.

472
00:17:42,460 --> 00:17:44,010
As long as it's used for legal business,

473
00:17:44,010 --> 00:17:45,740
it's not illegal fundraising.

474
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:47,880
Alright.

475
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,700
With a police officer backing me up,

476
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:50,720
I'm relieved.

477
00:17:51,310 --> 00:17:52,290
I support you.

478
00:17:53,290 --> 00:17:54,350
I'll give 100,000.

479
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:55,290
Mom.

480
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:57,170
Since a police officer is backing you up,

481
00:17:57,170 --> 00:17:57,810
just withdraw

482
00:17:57,810 --> 00:17:58,740
all your fixed deposits.

483
00:17:58,740 --> 00:17:59,740
-Enough.
-No way.

484
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:01,040
Don't eye Mom's

485
00:18:01,050 --> 00:18:02,240
measly savings.

486
00:18:03,090 --> 00:18:03,830
I'll cover

487
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:05,180
the remaining 900,000.

488
00:18:07,330 --> 00:18:08,070
But I can't give

489
00:18:08,070 --> 00:18:09,010
any more than that.

490
00:18:09,010 --> 00:18:10,050
My business's working capital

491
00:18:10,050 --> 00:18:10,630
can't be withdrawn.

492
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:11,960
Enough. That's enough.

493
00:18:12,850 --> 00:18:13,270
Shao,

494
00:18:13,290 --> 00:18:14,800
this 900,000 is more than enough.

495
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,500
You'll be my major shareholder.

496
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,200
Consider this money Mom's investment.

497
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,400
Mom is the major shareholder.

498
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:19,960
I don't want it.

499
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,130
You have to take it.

500
00:18:21,220 --> 00:18:22,760
Here, Mom, have some water.

501
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,940
Shao, have some water.

502
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:28,570
Stop pouring.

503
00:18:32,930 --> 00:18:33,390
Hello?

504
00:18:34,010 --> 00:18:34,640
Ju,

505
00:18:34,690 --> 00:18:35,610
can you talk?

506
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:37,440
I can. Go ahead.

507
00:18:37,810 --> 00:18:39,200
There's a new development
in the Wu Jiang case.

508
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,550
This Wu Jiang isn't Wu Jiang,

509
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,180
but we don't know

510
00:18:41,180 --> 00:18:42,510
if Wu Jiang even exists.

511
00:18:42,530 --> 00:18:43,000
Are you telling me

512
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,270
tongue twisters?

513
00:18:44,380 --> 00:18:44,830
The Yunnan police

514
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:45,890
just contacted us.

515
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,420
They said Wu Jiang's DNA

516
00:18:47,420 --> 00:18:48,200
matches a suspect

517
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:48,740
from a 1997

518
00:18:48,740 --> 00:18:49,720
drug trafficking case

519
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,350
in Yunnan.

520
00:18:51,210 --> 00:18:51,950
1997?

521
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:52,920
Yes.

522
00:18:53,310 --> 00:18:53,850
In 1997,

523
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,350
a drug dealer at the Yunnan border

524
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:57,120
had a shootout with anti-narcotics police.

525
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:58,090
He was injured while escaping

526
00:18:58,090 --> 00:18:59,180
and left bloodstains.

527
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:00,270
We can now confirm

528
00:19:00,350 --> 00:19:01,790
that this fugitive drug suspect

529
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:02,460
is him.

530
00:19:03,090 --> 00:19:03,920
That means...

531
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:05,040
This Wu Jiang,

532
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:06,730
the Vice President of Xinhai,

533
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,120
has a fake identity and resume.

534
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:10,780
Then do you know Li Yongqiang?

535
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,610
Li Yongqiang?

536
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:15,920
Do you know Wang Fumin?

537
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:17,680
This Wu Jiang at Xinhai

538
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,920
we investigated

539
00:19:19,030 --> 00:19:19,570
is not the original Wu Jiang

540
00:19:19,570 --> 00:19:21,230
from Mazhi Hongyuan Freight.

541
00:19:21,330 --> 00:19:21,920
When Captain Duojie had the accident,

542
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:23,570
he was in Yunnan.

543
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,650
He has an alibi.

544
00:19:25,930 --> 00:19:26,500
So,

545
00:19:26,890 --> 00:19:27,660
it couldn't be him

546
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:29,190
who killed Captain Duojie.

547
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,360
[Yunnan Police Crack 17-Year-Old Case;
Former Drug Dealer Turned Company VP]

548
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,490
That means

549
00:19:34,070 --> 00:19:35,190
the prime suspect

550
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:35,900
you're tracking now

551
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:37,200
has a fake identity.

552
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:40,380
He isn't Wu Jiang.

553
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:45,650
Doesn't this mean
we're back to square one?

554
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,200
So up until now,

555
00:19:47,570 --> 00:19:48,290
we can't confirm the person

556
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:49,010
who killed the Captain

557
00:19:49,010 --> 00:19:49,640
is Wu Jiang,

558
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:50,740
nor can we prove the body

559
00:19:50,740 --> 00:19:51,600
is the Captain.

560
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:52,760
So what have we actually investigated?

561
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:53,890
Calm down.

562
00:19:59,850 --> 00:20:00,790
At least one thing

563
00:20:00,790 --> 00:20:01,650
is certain now.

564
00:20:02,730 --> 00:20:03,380
Someone,

565
00:20:03,810 --> 00:20:05,010
or perhaps an organization,

566
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:06,200
wants us to believe the body

567
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:06,960
is the Captain

568
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:08,560
and the murderer is Wu Jiang.

569
00:20:09,460 --> 00:20:10,790
And they killed Wu Jiang

570
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,690
because they want the police
to close the case

571
00:20:12,690 --> 00:20:13,830
and bury the truth of this matter

572
00:20:13,830 --> 00:20:15,140
forever.

573
00:20:15,810 --> 00:20:16,660
Didn't we suspect

574
00:20:16,660 --> 00:20:17,440
another person

575
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,330
before?

576
00:20:19,030 --> 00:20:20,290
What is his name again?

577
00:20:20,860 --> 00:20:21,710
Wang Fumin.

578
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:22,830
Right.

579
00:20:23,850 --> 00:20:24,960
Right after the Captain went missing,

580
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,290
he ran off to South Asia.

581
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,130
This guy is highly suspicious.

582
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,770
How about I go to South Asia?

583
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:33,290
When I first bought my car,

584
00:20:33,290 --> 00:20:34,200
I drove there myself.

585
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,190
I know the route pretty well.

586
00:20:35,190 --> 00:20:36,120
What do you know?

587
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,350
How are you going to find him?

588
00:20:37,350 --> 00:20:38,420
There's been no news of him

589
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:39,240
2 years after he left the country.

590
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:40,640
We don't know if he's dead or alive!

591
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:41,220
Even his son

592
00:20:41,220 --> 00:20:42,080
can't find him!

593
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:43,330
You certainly can't!

594
00:20:43,330 --> 00:20:44,240
Since nothing works,

595
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:46,040
let's just stop investigating!

596
00:20:46,110 --> 00:20:46,940
You go be a security guard,

597
00:20:46,940 --> 00:20:48,000
and I'll go herd my cows!

598
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,070
That way, everyone is happy!

599
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:50,030
What are you saying?

600
00:20:50,030 --> 00:20:51,380
Who said we're not investigating?

601
00:20:51,380 --> 00:20:52,400
How are you going to find him there?

602
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,730
What's the noise about?

603
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:14,470
Look.

604
00:21:14,570 --> 00:21:15,460
This big patch.

605
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:17,250
It has grown well

606
00:21:17,660 --> 00:21:19,320
because we got plenty of rain.

607
00:21:19,950 --> 00:21:21,010
Look at this patch.

608
00:21:22,450 --> 00:21:23,580
This one isn't good.

609
00:21:24,180 --> 00:21:25,160
The slope is too steep

610
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,300
to hold water and soil.

611
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:27,660
I'll have to redo it later.

612
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:28,590
Look over there.

613
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:30,280
Nothing has grown at all.

614
00:21:33,930 --> 00:21:34,770
But

615
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:35,720
with the way

616
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:37,350
you guys scatter seeds,

617
00:21:37,370 --> 00:21:39,230
I bet half of them just fed the birds.

618
00:21:39,230 --> 00:21:40,360
Too inefficient.

619
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,870
There's a shotcrete machine
used in underground mines,

620
00:21:43,870 --> 00:21:46,140
mixing the soil, sheep dung,

621
00:21:46,380 --> 00:21:47,340
and grass seeds together.

622
00:21:47,340 --> 00:21:48,020
You can add a bit of water,

623
00:21:48,020 --> 00:21:49,690
then spray it directly onto the slope.

624
00:21:49,690 --> 00:21:51,100
It's fast and even.

625
00:21:52,260 --> 00:21:53,920
You always have so many ideas.

626
00:21:54,350 --> 00:21:55,050
A shotcrete machine

627
00:21:55,050 --> 00:21:56,250
isn't cheap.

628
00:21:56,660 --> 00:21:57,500
I won't see results

629
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,460
anytime soon.

630
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,800
Without cash flow,

631
00:21:59,930 --> 00:22:00,480
whatever I do,

632
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:02,010
I have to consider the cost.

633
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:03,350
I have connections.

634
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:04,290
We can rent one

635
00:22:04,670 --> 00:22:06,010
for 30% of the price.

636
00:22:07,170 --> 00:22:08,600
T-Thirty...

637
00:22:11,270 --> 00:22:12,400
Later, I will go back

638
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,650
and run the numbers.

639
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,320
I need to check the budget

640
00:22:15,330 --> 00:22:16,000
and think about it.

641
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,000
Don't wait.

642
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,180
Decide now.

643
00:22:18,940 --> 00:22:20,310
I'll give you 10 seconds.

644
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:21,480
Or I'm out.

645
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,180
10.

646
00:22:24,830 --> 00:22:25,160
9.

647
00:22:26,010 --> 00:22:26,460
8.

648
00:22:26,610 --> 00:22:27,310
Chun.

649
00:22:27,530 --> 00:22:27,800
7.

650
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:28,350
You're not even

651
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:29,610
trying to discuss this.

652
00:22:29,610 --> 00:22:30,140
You...

653
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:31,290
Fine, fine.

654
00:22:31,420 --> 00:22:31,750
Fine.

655
00:22:32,220 --> 00:22:33,310
Go ahead and do it.

656
00:22:33,730 --> 00:22:34,370
I've been worrying about

657
00:22:34,370 --> 00:22:35,700
low efficiency anyway.

658
00:22:36,820 --> 00:22:38,280
Just wait for the results.

659
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:39,230
I'm off.

660
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:56,940
Hello?

661
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:58,200
Meng.

662
00:22:58,740 --> 00:23:00,010
You really forget people

663
00:23:00,010 --> 00:23:01,640
once you're done with them.

664
00:23:02,450 --> 00:23:03,490
I remember paying you

665
00:23:03,490 --> 00:23:04,960
every single penny.

666
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:06,980
Take the money, close the shop,

667
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,170
take your people,

668
00:23:08,730 --> 00:23:09,860
and never come back.

669
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:10,950
Meng.

670
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:13,310
That'll cost extra.

671
00:23:14,050 --> 00:23:15,650
You want me to close the shop,

672
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,160
but what about after that?

673
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,060
Ding and I

674
00:23:18,090 --> 00:23:20,110
have mouths to feed.

675
00:23:21,220 --> 00:23:22,040
Okay, I got it.

676
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,170
I'll add more money.

677
00:23:24,630 --> 00:23:26,230
Pick it up at the usual place.

678
00:23:26,850 --> 00:23:27,740
Shen,

679
00:23:28,420 --> 00:23:29,950
don't be like someone else.

680
00:23:30,270 --> 00:23:31,670
Quit while you're ahead.

681
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:55,370
Coming! Coming!

682
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:57,380
Leader.

683
00:23:57,490 --> 00:23:58,690
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

684
00:24:00,980 --> 00:24:01,970
You're on the clock.

685
00:24:01,970 --> 00:24:02,710
Where did you go?

686
00:24:02,710 --> 00:24:03,770
I ate something bad

687
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:05,740
and had to use the bathroom.

688
00:24:08,210 --> 00:24:09,880
Go get some medicine from the infirmary.

689
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:10,810
Thanks, Leader.

690
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:20,820
Talk to me.

691
00:24:20,950 --> 00:24:22,040
Any news?

692
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:23,810
It's right up there.

693
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:26,770
That Wang Fumin

694
00:24:27,310 --> 00:24:28,670
didn't even resign

695
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:30,130
or take his salary.

696
00:24:30,730 --> 00:24:31,730
He just vanished.

697
00:24:34,250 --> 00:24:35,510
Same as what we knew.

698
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:37,360
What about the real Wu Jiang?

699
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:38,420
Haven't found him.

700
00:24:39,170 --> 00:24:39,830
Don't know.

701
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:43,050
I'm late.

702
00:24:46,870 --> 00:24:47,930
Pour me some water.

703
00:24:50,250 --> 00:24:52,180
Although the fake Wu Jiang is dead,

704
00:24:52,180 --> 00:24:53,710
I've been working at Xinhai

705
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:54,900
for over a month now,

706
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:57,080
and I've finally got onto the night shift.

707
00:24:57,080 --> 00:24:57,500
I took some

708
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:59,160
interesting footage inside.

709
00:24:59,180 --> 00:25:00,310
Do you want to see it?

710
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:01,760
Hurry up.

711
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:04,590
It concerns you.

712
00:25:04,810 --> 00:25:06,120
Me?

713
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:17,770
Sir!

714
00:25:18,970 --> 00:25:20,430
Are there any trucks behind you?

715
00:25:20,430 --> 00:25:21,610
No, I'm the last one.

716
00:25:22,140 --> 00:25:23,050
Is something wrong?

717
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:23,740
No.

718
00:25:24,080 --> 00:25:25,350
I'm covering a shift today.

719
00:25:25,350 --> 00:25:26,140
I'm a little sleepy,

720
00:25:26,140 --> 00:25:27,460
so I want to nap for a bit.

721
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:28,410
Okay, go ahead.

722
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:29,050
It'll be a while

723
00:25:29,050 --> 00:25:30,010
before we come down.

724
00:25:30,010 --> 00:25:30,470
Really?

725
00:25:31,070 --> 00:25:31,530
Okay.

726
00:25:31,610 --> 00:25:32,440
Drive safe.

727
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:33,130
Okay, okay.

728
00:26:38,350 --> 00:26:39,280
Coming! Coming!

729
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:40,980
Leader.

730
00:26:41,220 --> 00:26:42,220
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

731
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:43,280
I ate something bad

732
00:26:43,520 --> 00:26:45,050
and had to use the bathroom.

733
00:27:00,450 --> 00:27:01,350
Han, listen.

734
00:27:01,910 --> 00:27:03,350
I tried everything

735
00:27:03,380 --> 00:27:05,110
but couldn't get these photos.

736
00:27:05,250 --> 00:27:06,950
Is this illegal mining?

737
00:27:07,780 --> 00:27:08,610
Very likely.

738
00:27:09,970 --> 00:27:11,030
I also filmed this.

739
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:13,770
Look.

740
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:15,480
During the day,

741
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:16,880
very few trucks go up to the mine.

742
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:17,900
But at night, the number of coal trucks

743
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:18,770
skyrockets.

744
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:20,590
Doesn't this mean

745
00:27:21,290 --> 00:27:22,000
that after the mining ban,

746
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:22,680
Xinhai has never

747
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:23,880
stopped production?

748
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:26,740
Han, I think

749
00:27:26,770 --> 00:27:28,900
you have a gift for being an informant.

750
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:31,480
Really.

751
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:32,090
Is that so?

752
00:27:32,090 --> 00:27:33,620
I even ran into Meng Yaohui,

753
00:27:33,920 --> 00:27:35,450
and he didn't even catch me.

754
00:27:36,210 --> 00:27:37,280
Next time, can you

755
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,910
film the mining area directly?

756
00:27:38,910 --> 00:27:39,950
Take a video,

757
00:27:40,070 --> 00:27:41,110
to make the chain of evidence complete

758
00:27:41,110 --> 00:27:42,770
and leave Xinhai speechless.

759
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:44,850
Later on,

760
00:27:44,850 --> 00:27:45,440
I'll get you

761
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:46,440
a pinhole camera,

762
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:47,180
okay?

763
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:49,010
Yeah.

764
00:27:49,380 --> 00:27:51,490
Since you care about the environment,

765
00:27:51,490 --> 00:27:52,920
you can just follow Shao

766
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,530
and do undercover work.

767
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,290
You don't know.

768
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:57,370
I can't get in

769
00:27:57,370 --> 00:27:58,700
that mining area at all.

770
00:27:58,880 --> 00:27:59,940
The road is full of patrols

771
00:27:59,940 --> 00:28:00,980
at night.

772
00:28:02,500 --> 00:28:03,500
It's very strict.

773
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,740
We'll have to think of another way.

774
00:28:06,740 --> 00:28:08,130
Stop thinking about it.

775
00:28:08,550 --> 00:28:09,460
If you get caught,

776
00:28:09,460 --> 00:28:10,630
even Bai Chun can't save you.

777
00:28:10,630 --> 00:28:11,500
I know.

778
00:28:12,270 --> 00:28:13,030
I was thinking of

779
00:28:13,030 --> 00:28:14,630
posting it online directly.

780
00:28:14,740 --> 00:28:15,700
But then I thought,

781
00:28:15,700 --> 00:28:16,460
I was afraid of implicating

782
00:28:16,460 --> 00:28:17,440
Bai Chun,

783
00:28:17,460 --> 00:28:18,320
who got me into the mine.

784
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:19,380
So I didn't post it.

785
00:28:20,770 --> 00:28:21,290
Keep backups

786
00:28:21,290 --> 00:28:22,640
of these photos,

787
00:28:22,850 --> 00:28:23,370
wait until the chain of evidence

788
00:28:23,370 --> 00:28:24,460
is complete,

789
00:28:24,610 --> 00:28:27,070
then submit everything to the authorities.

790
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:31,090
I don't want to.

791
00:28:32,750 --> 00:28:34,450
The bosses at Xinhai

792
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,460
and the city leaders

793
00:28:36,460 --> 00:28:36,960
are all

794
00:28:36,990 --> 00:28:38,120
thick as thieves.

795
00:28:38,210 --> 00:28:39,260
Everyone knows that.

796
00:28:39,260 --> 00:28:40,790
The moment I hand this over,

797
00:28:40,850 --> 00:28:41,520
it'll end up right

798
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:42,850
in Meng Yaohui's hands.

799
00:28:43,030 --> 00:28:44,080
I'm not an idiot.

800
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:54,370
Here.

801
00:28:54,380 --> 00:28:55,110
Chun, let me.

802
00:28:56,270 --> 00:28:57,240
-Let me. Let me.
-It's okay. It's okay.

803
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,160
It's not heavy. It's not heavy.

804
00:28:58,160 --> 00:28:59,020
It's not heavy.

805
00:29:01,590 --> 00:29:02,240
Um,

806
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:04,250
there's something
I want to talk to you about.

807
00:29:04,250 --> 00:29:04,850
What is it?

808
00:29:06,380 --> 00:29:07,860
How is Xinhai's regreening project

809
00:29:07,860 --> 00:29:08,950
coming along?

810
00:29:11,030 --> 00:29:12,490
Planning another investigative report?

811
00:29:12,490 --> 00:29:13,090
No, no, no.

812
00:29:13,090 --> 00:29:13,920
Just curious.

813
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:15,000
After all,

814
00:29:15,020 --> 00:29:16,350
it's a key city project.

815
00:29:21,780 --> 00:29:23,440
Chun, I'm curious.

816
00:29:23,810 --> 00:29:24,790
You've worked in coal mines

817
00:29:24,790 --> 00:29:25,770
for so many years.

818
00:29:25,770 --> 00:29:27,300
You know better than anyone

819
00:29:27,590 --> 00:29:28,330
that the regreening project

820
00:29:28,330 --> 00:29:29,530
is a losing business.

821
00:29:30,050 --> 00:29:31,380
Just sowing grass seeds

822
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:32,830
and preventing soil erosion

823
00:29:32,830 --> 00:29:34,720
require a huge investment.

824
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:37,520
It doesn't make financial sense.

825
00:29:38,180 --> 00:29:39,420
Xinhai has no background

826
00:29:39,420 --> 00:29:40,140
in environmental protection,

827
00:29:40,140 --> 00:29:41,190
so why would a private company like it

828
00:29:41,190 --> 00:29:41,790
be willing

829
00:29:41,790 --> 00:29:42,920
to operate at a loss?

830
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:47,900
The policy has changed.

831
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:48,920
The state requires

832
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,090
ecological restoration of mines.

833
00:29:50,090 --> 00:29:51,850
Regreening is a mandatory target.

834
00:29:51,850 --> 00:29:53,420
Xinhai is answering the call.

835
00:29:53,420 --> 00:29:55,070
They must do it regardless of the cost.

836
00:29:55,070 --> 00:29:57,200
"Regardless of cost" is just a slogan.

837
00:29:57,480 --> 00:29:58,160
The Xinhai bosses

838
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,620
aren't philanthropists.

839
00:29:59,850 --> 00:30:01,220
You should know
the operating costs of coal mines

840
00:30:01,220 --> 00:30:02,540
better than I do.

841
00:30:02,660 --> 00:30:04,160
Money flows out like water

842
00:30:04,180 --> 00:30:05,180
every single day.

843
00:30:05,540 --> 00:30:06,670
Would you do it?

844
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:09,530
What do you mean by that?

845
00:30:11,550 --> 00:30:13,280
How much outcrop coal is there?

846
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:14,710
Can it cover

847
00:30:14,730 --> 00:30:15,990
the regreening costs?

848
00:30:16,820 --> 00:30:18,470
If funds aren't enough,

849
00:30:18,660 --> 00:30:19,480
is it possible

850
00:30:20,420 --> 00:30:21,360
that they...

851
00:30:21,380 --> 00:30:22,840
What are you trying to say?

852
00:30:24,340 --> 00:30:25,440
Is it possible that they're engaged in

853
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:26,370
illegal mining?

854
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,610
You're something else.

855
00:30:33,980 --> 00:30:35,220
You really are.

856
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:36,870
You shouldn't be a reporter.

857
00:30:36,870 --> 00:30:38,270
You should write novels.

858
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:40,850
You're getting better and better
at telling stories.

859
00:30:40,850 --> 00:30:41,910
I just feel like this whole thing

860
00:30:41,910 --> 00:30:43,040
doesn't make sense.

861
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:44,220
I'm just a shallow guy.

862
00:30:44,220 --> 00:30:45,370
I put money first.

863
00:30:45,460 --> 00:30:46,650
You probably think this

864
00:30:46,650 --> 00:30:47,240
sounds

865
00:30:47,270 --> 00:30:48,110
so ridiculous,

866
00:30:48,110 --> 00:30:49,640
like I'm talking nonsense.

867
00:30:49,790 --> 00:30:50,250
That's because

868
00:30:50,250 --> 00:30:51,390
you have principles

869
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:52,370
and a bottom line at work.

870
00:30:52,370 --> 00:30:53,040
But that doesn't mean

871
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:53,750
everyone at Xinhai

872
00:30:53,750 --> 00:30:54,570
is like you.

873
00:30:55,420 --> 00:30:56,950
I don't mean anything else.

874
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:58,980
I just want to give you a heads-up.

875
00:30:59,330 --> 00:31:00,930
Don't get dragged into this.

876
00:31:04,580 --> 00:31:05,200
I've worked in the mines

877
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,250
for over 10 years.

878
00:31:06,900 --> 00:31:08,580
I've heard of mining beyond boundaries.

879
00:31:08,580 --> 00:31:10,610
I've heard of destructive mining too.

880
00:31:10,610 --> 00:31:12,180
But I've never even heard

881
00:31:12,230 --> 00:31:13,290
of illegal mining.

882
00:31:18,770 --> 00:31:19,300
Alright.

883
00:31:21,590 --> 00:31:22,140
Well,

884
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:23,270
if you think everything is fine,

885
00:31:23,270 --> 00:31:25,130
then just forget I said anything.

886
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:33,320
What time do you start work tomorrow?

887
00:31:37,190 --> 00:31:38,990
Why aren't you saying anything?

888
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:40,700
Don't you want to chat?

889
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:47,570
You type really slow.

890
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:49,580
I was hoping

891
00:31:49,610 --> 00:31:51,110
to video chat with you.

892
00:31:51,420 --> 00:31:52,460
But now I can't even

893
00:31:52,460 --> 00:31:53,410
hear your voice.

894
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:00,020
You know what chatting like this

895
00:32:00,020 --> 00:32:01,180
reminds me of?

896
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:02,560
Streamers.

897
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:04,550
Streamers?

898
00:32:05,380 --> 00:32:07,040
Do you watch livestreams too?

899
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:09,260
I saw a livestreaming app

900
00:32:09,290 --> 00:32:10,830
on your phone last time.

901
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:13,050
I knew you liked watching them.

902
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:15,770
Alright.

903
00:32:16,270 --> 00:32:17,220
Stop talking.

904
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:19,280
Your workers will beat you up later.

905
00:32:19,450 --> 00:32:21,120
If you're free after work tomorrow,

906
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:22,650
I'll pick you up for dinner.

907
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:25,240
Why are you up so late,

908
00:32:25,340 --> 00:32:26,240
talking and laughing?

909
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,300
What are you doing?

910
00:32:28,350 --> 00:32:28,850
Mom.

911
00:32:29,610 --> 00:32:30,370
It's the middle of the night.

912
00:32:30,370 --> 00:32:31,970
Who are you on the phone with?

913
00:32:33,120 --> 00:32:33,710
A friend.

914
00:32:34,540 --> 00:32:35,560
A man or a woman?

915
00:32:36,470 --> 00:32:37,640
A man.

916
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,460
He's in Guangzhou?

917
00:32:41,770 --> 00:32:42,370
Since he's in Guangzhou,

918
00:32:42,370 --> 00:32:44,230
you asked him to dinner tomorrow?

919
00:32:48,850 --> 00:32:49,890
Tell him

920
00:32:50,620 --> 00:32:52,620
to set a time to come here for dinner.

921
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:56,250
Turn off your phone.

922
00:32:56,290 --> 00:32:56,950
Go to sleep.

923
00:33:08,430 --> 00:33:10,090
Did you hear all that just now?

924
00:33:10,380 --> 00:33:12,580
My mom wants you to come over for dinner.

925
00:33:13,290 --> 00:33:14,030
Han.

926
00:33:15,420 --> 00:33:16,280
Chives and egg.

927
00:33:17,290 --> 00:33:18,010
I remember that one time

928
00:33:18,010 --> 00:33:18,820
I made this filling,

929
00:33:18,820 --> 00:33:19,800
and you really liked it.

930
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:20,460
Yes, yes.

931
00:33:21,450 --> 00:33:22,980
Times were tough back then,

932
00:33:23,310 --> 00:33:24,510
so I only used one egg.

933
00:33:25,130 --> 00:33:26,650
Today I used 3 eggs.

934
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:28,830
Thank you. Thank you, Director Zhang.

935
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:32,140
Oh, you.

936
00:33:33,140 --> 00:33:33,950
You used to

937
00:33:33,980 --> 00:33:35,440
come to my house every day.

938
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:36,940
But you didn't visit me

939
00:33:36,940 --> 00:33:38,310
all these years.

940
00:33:40,830 --> 00:33:42,360
So much happened back then.

941
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:44,500
I was too embarrassed to come.

942
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:45,820
Don't say that.

943
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:47,120
Zhacuo still sends me

944
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:47,820
yak jerky

945
00:33:47,850 --> 00:33:49,250
from time to time.

946
00:33:49,350 --> 00:33:50,030
Back then,

947
00:33:50,050 --> 00:33:50,800
when Sangba was in the county town,

948
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:52,060
we still kept in touch.

949
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:52,760
Once,

950
00:33:52,790 --> 00:33:54,000
I took a research team

951
00:33:54,030 --> 00:33:54,750
to the conservation station,

952
00:33:54,750 --> 00:33:56,480
and he was the one who hosted us.

953
00:33:56,500 --> 00:33:57,420
You just don't consider me

954
00:33:57,420 --> 00:33:58,400
family,

955
00:33:58,420 --> 00:34:00,480
always calling me "Director Zhang."

956
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:04,930
Tastes good.

957
00:34:06,090 --> 00:34:07,290
Tastes just the same.

958
00:34:07,310 --> 00:34:08,920
I added 3 eggs.

959
00:34:08,969 --> 00:34:10,500
How could it taste the same?

960
00:34:11,110 --> 00:34:12,110
It's even better.

961
00:34:14,750 --> 00:34:16,610
Bai Ju told me about your situation

962
00:34:16,610 --> 00:34:18,420
a few times over the years.

963
00:34:20,429 --> 00:34:22,080
You've always been like this,

964
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:23,679
keeping everything inside.

965
00:34:25,290 --> 00:34:27,020
It's good in a way, but also bad.

966
00:34:27,610 --> 00:34:28,540
Good for others,

967
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:30,239
but bad for yourself.

968
00:34:32,420 --> 00:34:33,670
One time,

969
00:34:33,699 --> 00:34:34,909
Bai Ju arrested you.

970
00:34:35,580 --> 00:34:37,040
You said something to her.

971
00:34:37,270 --> 00:34:38,830
She came back and told me.

972
00:34:40,480 --> 00:34:42,040
I felt bad for a long time.

973
00:34:43,449 --> 00:34:44,260
You said,

974
00:34:45,550 --> 00:34:47,679
"Now that the Mountain Patrol is gone,

975
00:34:48,380 --> 00:34:49,710
no one looks after you."

976
00:34:56,510 --> 00:34:58,030
You still have me.

977
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:03,690
From now on,

978
00:35:05,330 --> 00:35:06,460
I'll look after you.

979
00:35:15,720 --> 00:35:16,320
Thank you.

980
00:35:18,170 --> 00:35:19,570
Thank you, Auntie Zhang.

981
00:35:22,380 --> 00:35:23,230
Alright.

982
00:35:23,640 --> 00:35:24,960
He's here to eat.

983
00:35:25,910 --> 00:35:26,900
Yes, yes.

984
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:27,840
Yes.

985
00:35:29,110 --> 00:35:29,740
Enough talk. Enough talk.

986
00:35:29,740 --> 00:35:30,490
Let's eat.

987
00:35:31,980 --> 00:35:32,960
Eat more, Han.

988
00:35:33,070 --> 00:35:33,630
Here.

989
00:35:41,510 --> 00:35:42,440
By the way, Han.

990
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,960
Do you have something to say?

991
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:46,970
Why did you decide

992
00:35:47,030 --> 00:35:48,280
to visit me today?

993
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:14,450
Please show me

994
00:36:14,470 --> 00:36:15,600
your Mine No. 2 pass.

995
00:36:16,750 --> 00:36:17,270
Here.

996
00:36:18,980 --> 00:36:20,910
Manager Bai, what brings you here?

997
00:36:21,210 --> 00:36:22,140
Lift the bar.

998
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:22,830
Manager Bai,

999
00:36:22,830 --> 00:36:23,690
you can't go in.

1000
00:36:24,070 --> 00:36:25,530
The mining area has rules.

1001
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:26,550
Vehicles and personnel

1002
00:36:26,550 --> 00:36:27,280
without the blue pass for Mine No. 2

1003
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,000
are not allowed

1004
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:28,930
to enter.

1005
00:36:30,940 --> 00:36:32,200
Don't you know who I am?

1006
00:36:32,650 --> 00:36:33,360
Manager Bai,

1007
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:33,940
who in Xinhai

1008
00:36:33,940 --> 00:36:35,280
doesn't know you?

1009
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:36,470
Then let me through.

1010
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:39,570
Look,

1011
00:36:39,690 --> 00:36:40,320
they just installed

1012
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,650
this camera yesterday.

1013
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,380
If I let you in against the rules,

1014
00:36:43,380 --> 00:36:44,510
I'll get fined.

1015
00:36:44,630 --> 00:36:46,560
Please don't make this hard for me.

1016
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:47,670
Why don't you

1017
00:36:47,740 --> 00:36:48,860
call Mr. Meng

1018
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:50,290
and ask for permission?

1019
00:36:53,290 --> 00:36:54,020
Manager Bai.

1020
00:36:56,830 --> 00:36:57,440
Forget it.

1021
00:37:03,290 --> 00:37:04,690
Let me see your pass.

1022
00:37:14,540 --> 00:37:15,210
Bai Chun,

1023
00:37:15,660 --> 00:37:16,440
your Mine No. 1

1024
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:18,100
has been pretty quiet lately.

1025
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:19,440
How do you have time

1026
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:20,660
to come to Mine No. 2?

1027
00:37:23,620 --> 00:37:24,150
Mr. Meng.

1028
00:37:25,940 --> 00:37:26,400
At Mine No. 1,

1029
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:28,130
during the slope maintenance,

1030
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:29,410
the daily amount

1031
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:31,090
of residual and outcrop coal cleared out

1032
00:37:31,090 --> 00:37:31,570
is only enough

1033
00:37:31,570 --> 00:37:32,970
for one transport shift.

1034
00:37:33,780 --> 00:37:34,730
But I heard

1035
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:36,920
the transport team at Mine No. 2

1036
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:38,570
is not only working 3 shifts

1037
00:37:38,570 --> 00:37:40,170
but has also increased their trips.

1038
00:37:40,170 --> 00:37:40,770
So I wanted

1039
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:41,980
to go into Mine No. 2

1040
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,530
and learn a thing or two.

1041
00:37:46,650 --> 00:37:47,230
Bai Chun,

1042
00:37:48,570 --> 00:37:50,130
you've really matured.

1043
00:37:51,580 --> 00:37:53,480
You've learned to talk in circles.

1044
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:54,620
Then I'll be straight with you.

1045
00:37:54,620 --> 00:37:56,550
Things aren't like they used to be.

1046
00:37:56,550 --> 00:37:57,820
Sloppy work

1047
00:37:57,930 --> 00:37:59,120
and failing dust control standards

1048
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:00,350
are minor details.

1049
00:38:00,510 --> 00:38:02,010
Problems can be fixed.

1050
00:38:02,190 --> 00:38:04,050
But with the mining ban in effect,

1051
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:05,590
digging even one more shovel

1052
00:38:05,590 --> 00:38:06,510
is illegal mining.

1053
00:38:06,510 --> 00:38:08,110
You'll go to prison for that.

1054
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:10,240
Coal can't speak for itself.

1055
00:38:11,570 --> 00:38:12,460
It won't tell you

1056
00:38:12,460 --> 00:38:13,990
which piece is outcrop coal

1057
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:15,030
and which piece

1058
00:38:15,030 --> 00:38:16,490
is freshly mined raw coal.

1059
00:38:17,730 --> 00:38:19,090
After washing, dewatering,

1060
00:38:19,090 --> 00:38:20,290
drying, and grading,

1061
00:38:20,570 --> 00:38:21,690
once it's shipped out,

1062
00:38:21,690 --> 00:38:23,220
they all have just one name:

1063
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:24,400
commercial coal.

1064
00:38:27,770 --> 00:38:29,100
Am I right, Manager Bai?

1065
00:38:31,340 --> 00:38:31,990
I see.

1066
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:16,140
Who built this bench road?

1067
00:39:16,950 --> 00:39:18,310
The height is over the limit,

1068
00:39:18,310 --> 00:39:19,710
and it's not wide enough.

1069
00:39:19,740 --> 00:39:21,300
These are safety hazards.

1070
00:39:21,430 --> 00:39:22,850
And that working face over there,

1071
00:39:22,850 --> 00:39:23,630
2 months ago,

1072
00:39:23,650 --> 00:39:25,450
it was already mined to the edge.

1073
00:39:25,530 --> 00:39:26,510
But now stripping operations

1074
00:39:26,510 --> 00:39:27,570
are still ongoing.

1075
00:39:27,630 --> 00:39:29,000
This must be a violation.

1076
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,330
It's definitely not mining outcrop coal.

1077
00:39:32,490 --> 00:39:33,590
So, do you want

1078
00:39:34,290 --> 00:39:35,690
to take pictures of them?

1079
00:39:37,620 --> 00:39:38,620
Take pictures

1080
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:40,910
and send them to Shao Yunfei

1081
00:39:41,900 --> 00:39:43,030
to expose Xinhai for using

1082
00:39:43,030 --> 00:39:44,500
outcrop mining as a cover

1083
00:39:44,540 --> 00:39:45,670
for illegal mining.

1084
00:39:51,130 --> 00:39:53,590
That would be
the absolute right thing to do.

1085
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:54,810
And I won't stop you.

1086
00:39:59,180 --> 00:40:00,020
But Bai Chun,

1087
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:03,330
there are two sides to everything.

1088
00:40:03,650 --> 00:40:04,570
This is the side

1089
00:40:04,590 --> 00:40:05,800
we can all see.

1090
00:40:06,980 --> 00:40:08,640
But what about the other side?

1091
00:40:11,910 --> 00:40:12,940
What do you mean?

1092
00:40:15,950 --> 00:40:16,510
Them.

1093
00:40:18,650 --> 00:40:20,010
Their lives

1094
00:40:20,730 --> 00:40:22,080
will never be seen.

1095
00:40:25,370 --> 00:40:26,980
Yu, Liu,

1096
00:40:27,110 --> 00:40:28,240
they're down there.

1097
00:40:28,610 --> 00:40:29,190
And many other brothers

1098
00:40:29,190 --> 00:40:30,360
who worked with you

1099
00:40:30,380 --> 00:40:31,340
in Mine No. 1.

1100
00:40:32,790 --> 00:40:34,850
You should know them better than I do.

1101
00:40:36,980 --> 00:40:39,040
Coal mining is a high-risk industry,

1102
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:40,530
but why do they

1103
00:40:40,530 --> 00:40:42,530
insist on working on the front line?

1104
00:40:43,150 --> 00:40:43,610
Yes.

1105
00:40:44,180 --> 00:40:45,860
Mine No. 2 has safety issues.

1106
00:40:46,290 --> 00:40:47,070
Since you can notice,

1107
00:40:47,070 --> 00:40:48,190
can't they?

1108
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,490
But why does no one speak up?

1109
00:40:51,710 --> 00:40:52,710
Why do they continue

1110
00:40:52,710 --> 00:40:53,830
to work overtime?

1111
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:55,760
It's not necessarily true

1112
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,510
that they can only stay

1113
00:40:56,510 --> 00:40:57,550
in this one place.

1114
00:40:57,650 --> 00:40:58,210
The regreening project

1115
00:40:58,210 --> 00:40:59,280
can absorb some of them.

1116
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:01,130
But compared to mining,

1117
00:41:01,630 --> 00:41:03,290
does regreening pay the same?

1118
00:41:06,230 --> 00:41:07,400
Neither you nor I can bear

1119
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:09,140
the impact of shutting down production.

1120
00:41:09,140 --> 00:41:10,620
They and their families

1121
00:41:10,670 --> 00:41:11,940
can bear it even less.

1122
00:41:13,700 --> 00:41:15,300
Take your brother as an example.

1123
00:41:15,300 --> 00:41:16,480
He can switch to the regreening business

1124
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:16,860
because

1125
00:41:16,860 --> 00:41:18,320
he still has some capital.

1126
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:19,450
But what about them?

1127
00:41:20,810 --> 00:41:22,580
If they had any choice,

1128
00:41:23,190 --> 00:41:24,590
who would want to do this?

1129
00:41:30,300 --> 00:41:30,890
I'm also just

1130
00:41:30,890 --> 00:41:32,090
working for the boss.

1131
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,170
In my position,

1132
00:41:34,530 --> 00:41:36,210
being responsible to the boss,

1133
00:41:36,210 --> 00:41:38,250
making money for him,
and keeping him satisfied

1134
00:41:38,250 --> 00:41:39,230
are fine.

1135
00:41:41,030 --> 00:41:42,340
But I can also

1136
00:41:43,690 --> 00:41:44,800
think a little more

1137
00:41:44,820 --> 00:41:46,280
about the people under me.

1138
00:42:23,940 --> 00:42:25,400
When mining outcrop coal,

1139
00:42:27,160 --> 00:42:29,420
we still need to pay attention to safety.

1140
00:42:36,180 --> 00:42:36,910
Don't worry.

1141
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:39,620
I'll handle these issues.

1142
00:42:40,930 --> 00:42:43,260
You just focus on the regreening project.

1143
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:54,970
Hello, Mr. Meng.

1144
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:56,210
Hello, Mr. Meng.

1145
00:42:57,070 --> 00:42:57,940
Hello, Mr. Meng.

1146
00:42:57,940 --> 00:42:58,480
Hello, Mr. Meng.

1147
00:42:58,480 --> 00:42:59,100
Hello, Mr. Meng.
